OL,3,CMan jailed for stealing #397,000 from
OL,4,Cfamily firm to go on luxury trips
OL,6,FJersey's Royal Court heard how Mitton
OL,7,Fwas offered the job to help him get
OL,8,Fback into work, was paid well with
OL,9,Fbonuses and lived rent-free in a home
OL,10,Fowned by his father-in-law, but still
OL,11,Fstarted stealing almost immediately.
OL,13,FCommissioner Andrew Oldland explained
OL,14,Fthat Mitton showed no remorse,
OL,15,Fdeflecting blame onto other family
OL,16,Fmembers in a "particularly serious
OL,17,Fbreach of trust".
