OL,3,CMan jailed for stealing #397,000 from
OL,4,Cfamily firm to go on luxury trips
OL,6,FThe prosecution explained: "As a
OL,7,Fmember of the family, you were trusted
OL,8,Fwith sums of money, made a signatory
OL,9,Fand had keys to both safes. Rather
OL,10,Fthan improving financial systems, you
OL,11,Ftook advantage.
OL,13,F"You stole cash that had come from the
OL,14,Fbank and paid it into your own
OL,15,Faccounts. As quickly as this money
OL,16,Fcame in, it came out again."
OL,18,FIt was discovered that Mitton had paid
OL,19,Fmoney into his own account on the same
OL,20,Fday he took cash from the family
OL,21,Fbusiness on 30 occasions.
